{"lemma":"خالِد","slug":"خالِد","root":"خ.ل.د","root_slug":"خ-ل-د","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ل-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خالِد","root":"خلد","pos":"N","occurrence_count":74},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11244"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D8%AF"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"immortal; glorious; eternal"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Khalid or Khaled"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of the verb خَلَدَ (ḵalada)."},"ipa":["/xaː.lid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11244","headword_ar":"خَالِدٌ","root":"xld","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Remaining, staying,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxawaAlidu","text_ar":"الخَوَالِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaAlidapu","text_ar":"الخَالِدَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The three pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"portions, of stone,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rock, called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^avaAfiY","text_ar":"الاَثَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which the cooking-pot is placed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remaining in their places:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) so called because of their remaining (S, L) a long time (L) after the standing relies of a house have become effaced. (S, L.) [See an ex., from a poem of ElMukhabbal Es-Saadee, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", p. 78; where"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xwAld","text_ar":"خوالد"},{"kind":"text","text":"is with tenween for the sake of the metre.] ―         -b3-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The mountains:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the stones:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L. K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the rocks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called for the same reason. (L.)       -A2-  [As a proper name,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAlidN","text_ar":"خَالِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is often written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"x`lidN","text_ar":"خٰلِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","L","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%AE%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF/","headword_ar":"خالدون","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_39","lexicon_en":"ʿAbdullāh ibn ʿAbbās, Gharīb al-Qurʾān fī Shiʿr al-ʿArab, also known as Masāʾil Nāfiʿ b. al-Azraq (d. 687 CE)","lexicon_ar":"غريب القرآن في شعر العرب لعبد الله بن عباس","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=94265#99d701","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">خ ل د [خالدون]</span><br><span>قال: يا ابن عباس: أخبرني عن قول الله عزّ وجلّ: وَهُمْ فِيها خالِدُونَ .</span><br><span>قال: هم فيها باقون لا يخرجون منها أبدا، كذلك أهل النار وأهل الجنة.</span><br><span>قال: وهل تعرف العرب ذلك؟</span><br><span>قال: نعم، أما سمعت عدي بن زيد وهو يقول:</span><br><span>فهل من خالد إمّا هلكنا </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> وهل بالموت يا للنّاس عار </span><br><span>وقال لبيد بن ربيعة :</span><br><span>كلّ بني أم وإن كثروا </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> يوما يصيرون إلى واحد </span><br><span>فالواحد الباقي كمن قد مضى </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> ليس بمتروك ولا خالد </span>"}]}}